Title: Introduction
---
<h2 class="title">Wyam is a simple to use, highly modular, and extremely configurable static content generator. It can be used to generate web sites, scaffold development projects, create ebooks, and much more.</h2>

<p>It's currently under heavy development, but is usable today. Read on for more information if you want to get started now and help influence it's future direction.</p>

<div class="page-header"><h1>Features</h1></div>
<ul>
	<li>Flexible script-based configuration</li>
	<li>Lots of modules for things like reading and writing files, handling frontmatter, and manipulating metadata</li>
	<li>Integrated YAML parser</li>
	<li>Support for multiple templating languages including Razor</li>
	<li>Integrated web server for previewing output</li>
	<li>Integrated file watching and regeneration</li>
	<li>Full NuGet support</li>
	<li>Easily extensible</li>
	<li>Embeddable engine</li>
</ul>

